<subSubSection id="C30165293302FFC624918B06FDC8F9D7" box="[151,522,1590,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BA436A23302FFC624918B06FDC8F9D7" blockId="1.[151,522,1590,1617]" box="[151,522,1590,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<heading id="D0EC81CE3302FFC624918B06FDC8F9D7" bold="true" box="[151,522,1590,1617]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC624918B06FDC8F9D7" bold="true" box="[151,522,1590,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC624C98B06FEF5F9D7" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[207,311,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC624C98B06FEF5F9D7" bold="true" box="[207,311,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
generic complex
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30165293302FFC624918B4EFD00F883" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA436A23302FFC624918B4EFD00F883" blockId="1.[151,1437,1663,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
Male genitalia of the generic complex are characterized by the simple valva gradually tapering distally and lacking a corona and a costal process which are present in genera of the ‘ 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC6277D8B92FBCEF93B" box="[891,1036,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC6277D8B92FC2CF93B" box="[891,1006,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrochola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agrochola</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC6200D8B92FB71F93B" authority="Warren" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1910" box="[1035,1203,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Telorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC6200D8B92FB9AF93B" box="[1035,1112,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Telorta</emphasis>
Warren
</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC620C98B92FA5FF93B" authority="Warren" authorityName="Warren" box="[1231,1437,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyalobole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC620C98B92FA86F93B" box="[1231,1348,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Hyalobole</emphasis>
Warren
</taxonomicName>
generic complex’. In female genitalia, the well-developed antrum separated from the posterior section of the ductus bursae by a membranous section is characteristic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30165293302FFC524C18A3EFE64FE57" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="444" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA436A23302FFC524C18A3EFE64FE57" blockId="1.[151,1437,1663,2013]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="444" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B533302FFC624C18A3EFE7AF8AF" author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Yela, J. L. &amp; Hreblay, M." box="[199,440,1807,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" refId="ref7969" refString="Ronkay, L., Yela, J. L. &amp; Hreblay, M. (2001) Hadeninae II. Noctuidae Europaeae. Vol. 5. Entomological Press, Soro, 352 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Ronkay 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC6252E8A3EFEA1F8AF" box="[296,355,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
considered the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC626BA8A3EFCDCF8AF" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[700,798,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC626BA8A3EFCDCF8AF" box="[700,798,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a member of the ‘ 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC6201A8A3EFB3FF8AF" box="[1052,1277,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Agrochola-Conistra</emphasis>
generic complex’ comprising numerous genera in Eurasia and North America. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B533302FFC620258A02FAC9F8CB" author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[1059,1291,1843,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" refId="ref7916" refString="Ronkay, L., Ronkay, G., Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2017) Xyleninae I. The Agrochola generic complex. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Vol. 9. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 342 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Ronkay 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC620878A02FB78F8CB" box="[1153,1210,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
separated so called ‘conistroid’ genera (called here as the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC6268B8A66FD2DF8F7" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[653,751,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC6268B8A66FD2DF8F7" box="[653,751,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
generic complex) from the ‘ 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC620378A66FA5EF8F7" box="[1073,1436,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC620378A66FB66F8F7" box="[1073,1188,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrochola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agrochola</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC620C68A66FACFF8F7" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1910" box="[1216,1293,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Telorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Telorta</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC6212C8A66FA5EF8F7" box="[1322,1436,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyalobole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hyalobole</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
generic complex’. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B533302FFC625698A4AFDA0F813" author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Yela, J. L. &amp; Hreblay, M." box="[367,610,1915,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" refId="ref7969" refString="Ronkay, L., Yela, J. L. &amp; Hreblay, M. (2001) Hadeninae II. Noctuidae Europaeae. Vol. 5. Entomological Press, Soro, 352 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Ronkay 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC625D78A4AFDCFF813" box="[465,525,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
listed such Nearctic genera as 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC627D78A4AFB3DF813" authority="Franclemont" authorityName="Franclemont" authorityYear="1937" box="[977,1279,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Metaxaglaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC627D78A4AFBA1F813" box="[977,1123,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Metaxaglaea</emphasis>
Franclemont
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC6210B8A4AFEE7F83F" authority="Franclemont" authorityName="Franclemont" authorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Chaetaglaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC6210B8A4AFA5EF813" box="[1293,1436,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Chaetaglaea</emphasis>
Franclemont
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC6255B8AAEFDC9F83F" authority="Grote" authorityName="Grote" authorityYear="1878" box="[349,523,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Epiglaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC6255B8AAEFE00F83F" box="[349,450,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Epiglaea</emphasis>
Grote
</taxonomicName>
as closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC626FA8AAEFC9CF83F" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[764,862,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC626FA8AAEFC9CF83F" box="[764,862,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the male genitalia ground plan of these taxa is significantly different from that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC626728AF2FD14F85B" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[628,726,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC626728AF2FD14F85B" box="[628,726,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and closer to such 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC627B48AF2FBDBF85B" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1837" box="[946,1049,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Xylenina">Xylenina</taxonomicName>
genera as 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC620958AF2FA90F85B" authority="Snellen" authorityName="Snellen" authorityYear="1867" box="[1171,1362,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Spudaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC620958AF2FB31F85B" box="[1171,1267,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Spudaea</emphasis>
Snellen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213302FFC521588AF2FF2FFF37" authority="Hubner" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Jodia" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="444" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03302FFC621588AF2FA5EF85B" box="[1374,1436,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Jodia</emphasis>
Hübner
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213301FFC524FF8DA6FE50FF37" authority="Reisser" authorityName="Reisser" authorityYear="1930" box="[249,402,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Evisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC524FF8DA6FEF5FF36" box="[249,311,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Evisa</emphasis>
Reisser
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213301FFC525CA8DA6FD28FF37" authority="Hubner. Besides" authorityName="Hubner. Besides" box="[460,746,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eupsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC525CA8DA6FDEBFF37" box="[460,553,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Eupsilia</emphasis>
Hübner. Besides
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213301FFC526F58DA6FC97FF37" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[755,853,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC526F58DA6FC97FF37" box="[755,853,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we include in the generic complex the genus 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC5216F8DA6FF22FF52" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Suginistra</emphasis>
L. Ronkay, G. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B533301FFC525968D8AFD2FFF53" author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[400,749,187,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" refId="ref7916" refString="Ronkay, L., Ronkay, G., Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2017) Xyleninae I. The Agrochola generic complex. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Vol. 9. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 342 pp." type="book" year="2017">Ronkay, Gyulai &amp; Varga, 2017</bibRefCitation>
which was considered by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A4B533301FFC5201C8D8AFAC7FF53" author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[1050,1285,187,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" refId="ref7916" refString="Ronkay, L., Ronkay, G., Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2017) Xyleninae I. The Agrochola generic complex. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Vol. 9. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 342 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Ronkay 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC5207F8D8AFB71FF53" box="[1145,1203,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
as a member of the 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC524E68DEEFDEEFF7F" box="[224,556,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Agrochola-Telorta-Hyalobole</emphasis>
generic complex due to its external similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213301FFC5205C8DEEFB0DFF7F" box="[1114,1231,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrochola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC5205C8DEEFB0DFF7F" box="[1114,1231,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Agrochola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its allies, and three additional new genera described below. Nevertheless, it is worth mentioning that the subdivision of genera into ‘generic complexes’ as well as evaluation of their relationships based only on morphological features is quite subjective and artificial. 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC525B78C7AFDE6FEE3" box="[433,548,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Suginistra</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213301FFC526588C7AFD14FEE3" authority="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth, 2022" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth" authorityYear="2022" box="[606,726,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Vargalorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC526588C7AFD14FEE3" box="[606,726,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Vargalorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC526D88C7AFCEDFEE3" bold="true" box="[734,815,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25C57CB3301FFC526D88C7AFCEDFEE3" box="[734,815,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are probably transitional groups between the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213301FFC5213C8C7AFA5EFEE3" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[1338,1436,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC5213C8C7AFA5EFEE3" box="[1338,1436,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B96FEAB03301FFC524CF8C5EFDF7FE0F" box="[201,565,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213301FFC524CF8C5EFEFEFE0F" box="[201,316,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrochola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agrochola</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213301FFC5255F8C5EFE64FE0F" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1910" box="[345,422,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Telorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Telorta</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B4D213301FFC525C58C5EFDF7FE0F" box="[451,565,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyalobole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hyalobole</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
‘generic complexes’. The question on relationships between the genera and their status can be clarified by using molecular methods with numerous Palaearctic, Oriental and Nearctic groups included in the analysis.
</paragraph>
